The paper presents a new game semantics for Martin-Lof type theory, which is a topic in mathematical logic and theoretical computer science. The paper also discusses the interpretation of propositional equalities and the refutation of the principle of uniqueness of identity proofs, which are topics in logic and type theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also discusses the use of isomorphism strategies and the interpretation of equalities, which are topics in programming languages and formal methods, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.LF (Logic in Computer Science) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also uses game theory to develop the semantics, which makes cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the univalence axiom, which is a topic in homotopy type theory, making cs.CC (Computational Complexity) a possible sub-category as well.
